# Workspace Bootstrap

Use when runtime folders are missing, session tools fail to find `library/sessions/current/`, or the user asks to set up the workspace.

## Check status

```bash
python library/tools/scripts/setup_workspace.py --show
```

## Bootstrap (idempotent)

```bash
python library/tools/scripts/setup_workspace.py
```

Creates missing paths defined in `library/tools/scripts/setup_workspace.py` (`RUNTIME_DIRECTORIES`), including:

- `library/sessions/{current,recent,archived}/`
- `library/docs/` category folders
- `library/databases/{schemas,scripts,sources}/`
- `projects/`, `tests/`

## First-run marker

Fresh clones include `library/.workspace_setup_required`. Successful bootstrap removes it locally. Do not commit that deletion.

If the marker is gone but dirs are still missing, run bootstrap anyway.

## Pair external project (optional)

```bash
python library/tools/scripts/setup_workspace.py --pair my-app --project-path "D:/path/to/project"
```

## After bootstrap

Standard post-clone flow continues with MCP setup:

```bash
python library/tools/scripts/setup_database.py
```

Then reload the editor. See root `README.md` Quick Start.
